# Minimal Maison — RTL typography (v1.1 Phase 1)

Site locale is Persian (`fa-IR`, `dir="rtl"`). Under RTL, **`text-start` = reading-start (physical right)**. **`text-end` = inline-end (physical left)** and breaks multiline editorial alignment.

## `mm-editorial` — alignment owner

The **`mm-editorial`** primitive is the single source of truth for editorial RTL text alignment. It owns **`text-start` only** — no width, margin, padding, color, typography, or spacing.

Editorial surfaces inside `mm-editorial` **inherit alignment from the primitive root**. Do not set alignment on children:

- H1, H2, H3
- Lede / lead paragraphs
- Body copy
- Eyebrows
- Editorial CTA text (inline links in editorial columns)

```css
/* ✅ GOOD — primitive owns alignment; section wrapper owns layout */
.mm-hero-cinematic__content {
  @apply me-auto ms-0 w-full max-w-[36rem] ...;
}
.mm-editorial {
  @apply text-start;
}

/* ❌ FORBIDDEN — split alignment architecture */
.mm-hero-cinematic__content {
  @apply text-end;
}
.mm-hero-cinematic__heading {
  @apply text-start;
}
```

## Forbidden patterns

- **`text-end` on editorial wrappers**
- **Wrapper `text-end` + child `text-start`** (split alignment)
- **Child alignment overrides inside `mm-editorial`** (e.g. `text-start` on H1 when parent is `mm-editorial`)

## Allowed patterns (not editorial)

- **`text-center`** — symmetric modules (section headers, form intros, notices)
- **`justify-end` / `items-end`** — flex/grid layout chrome (header cart, bottom-aligned hero frame), not text alignment
- **`dir="ltr"`** + `text-start` — phone, email, URL, and numeric input islands

## Prefer logical utilities

Use `text-start`, `ms-*`, `me-*`, `ps-*`, `pe-*`, `border-s`. Avoid physical `text-left`, `text-right`, `ml-*`, `mr-*` unless LTR-isolated.
